<ul data-start="54" data-end="217">
<li data-start="54" data-end="108">
<p data-start="56" data-end="108">The <strong data-start="60" data-end="78">CSS is loading</strong> (dark background is applied).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="109" data-end="217">
<p data-start="111" data-end="217">But the <strong data-start="119" data-end="173">hero layout and cards are not positioned correctly</strong>, so everything looks stacked and oversized.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="219" data-end="312">This happens because the <strong data-start="244" data-end="311">right side container and image sizes need proper layout control</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="314" data-end="365">Let's fix it with a <strong data-start="334" data-end="364">simple and reliable layout</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="367" data-end="370">
